<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="121" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
We disagree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Stemmerik, JF" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" pagination="275 - 284" refId="B32" refString="Stemmerik, JF, 1964a. Flora Malesianae Precursores XXXVIII: Notes on Pisonia L. in the Old World (Nyctaginaceae). Blumea 12: 275 - 284" title="Flora Malesianae Precursores XXXVIII: Notes on Pisonia L. in the Old World (Nyctaginaceae)." volume="12" year="1964 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stemmerik’s">Stemmerik's</normalizedToken>
(1964a)
</bibRefCitation>
view on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Choisy" authorityYear="1849" baseAuthorityName="Poir." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Pisonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pisonia lanceolata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Pisonia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Poir.) Choisy, which he considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. umbellifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="umbellifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">P. umbellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Friedmann, F" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" pagination="383 - 392" refId="B14" refString="Friedmann, F, 1986. Etude de la structure du perianthe chez des Pisonia paleotropicaux et description de P. sechellarum sp. nov. (Nyctaginaceae). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle. Section B. Adansonia 8 (4): 383 - 392" title="Etude de la structure du perianthe chez des Pisonia paleotropicaux et description de P. sechellarum sp. nov. (Nyctaginaceae). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle. Section B." volume="8" year="1986">Friedmann (1986)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. lanceolata" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">P. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species with affinities to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. brunoniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="brunoniana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">P. brunoniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be distinguished by the pattern of incisions in the flower.
</paragraph>
